query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM movie_info_idx AS mi_idx JOIN info_type AS it2 ON it2.id = mi_idx.info_type_id AND it2.info = 'votes' JOIN title AS t ON t.id = mi_idx.movie_id JOIN (SELECT cn.id AS cn_id, mc.movie_id AS mc_movie_id, mc.company_id AS mc_company_id FROM movie_companies AS mc JOIN company_name AS cn ON cn.id = mc.company_id AND cn.name LIKE 'Lionsgate%') AS cn_mc ON t.id = cn_mc.mc_movie_id AND mi_idx.movie_id = cn_mc.mc_movie_id JOIN (SELECT mk.keyword_id AS mk_keyword_id, mk.movie_id AS mk_movie_id, k.id AS k_id FROM movie_keyword AS mk JOIN keyword AS k ON k.id = mk.keyword_id AND k.keyword IN ('murder', 'violence', 'blood', 'gore', 'death', 'female-nudity', 'hospital')) AS k_mk ON t.id = k_mk.mk_movie_id AND mi_idx.movie_id = k_mk.mk_movie_id AND k_mk.mk_movie_id = cn_mc.mc_movie_id JOIN cast_info AS ci ON t.id = ci.movie_id AND ci.movie_id = mi_idx.movie_id AND ci.movie_id = k_mk.mk_movie_id AND ci.movie_id = cn_mc.mc_movie_id AND ci.note IN ('(writer)', '(head writer)', '(written by)', '(story)', '(story editor)') JOIN name AS n ON n.id = ci.person_id JOIN (SELECT mi.info_type_id AS mi_info_type_id, mi.movie_id AS mi_movie_id, it1.id AS it1_id FROM movie_info AS mi JOIN info_type AS it1 ON it1.id = mi.info_type_id AND it1.info = 'genres' AND mi.info IN ('Horror', 'Action', 'Sci-Fi', 'Thriller', 'Crime', 'War')) AS it1_mi ON t.id = it1_mi.mi_movie_id AND ci.movie_id = it1_mi.mi_movie_id AND it1_mi.mi_movie_id = mi_idx.movie_id AND it1_mi.mi_movie_id = k_mk.mk_movie_id AND it1_mi.mi_movie_id = cn_mc.mc_movie_id
